{{Glossary
|Entry=Construct
|Description=A fully instantiated and lexicalized instance of a construction.

A construct analysis consists of:
the text
constructional information, including the lexeme(s), the construction, and frame(s)
constructional information of its constituents
bindings between entities in the cxns
metaphor information, including links to any metaphor entries

Form on English wiki: [[https://metaphor.icsi.berkeley.edu/en/index.php/Form:Construct_analysis]]
|Entered by=Elise
}}
